title: thread 'rustc' panicked at 'expression with never type wound up being adjusted'

labels.name: E-easy
labels.description: Call for participation: Experience needed to fix: Easy / not much (good first issue)

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
I'm seeing an internal compiler error on the following input, found by [fuzz-rustc](https://github.com/dwrensha/fuzz-rustc): ### Code ```Rust fn main() { 0.....{loop{}1} } ``` ### Error output ``` error: unexpected token: `...` --> src/main.rs:2:6 | 2 | 0.....{loop{}1} | ^^^ | help: use `..` for an exclusive range | 2 | 0....{loop{}1} | ~~ help: or `..=` for an inclusive range | 2 | 0..=..{loop{}1} | ~~~ warning: unreachable expression --> src/main.rs:2:18 | 2 | 0.....{loop{}1} | ------^ unreachable expression | | | any code following this expression is unreachable | = note: `#[warn(unreachable_code)]` on by default thread 'rustc' panicked at 'expression with never type wound up being adjusted', compiler/rustc_typeck/src/check/expr.rs:81:13 note: run with `RUST_BACKTRACE=1` environment variable to display a backtrace ``` The ICE happens after reporting some other errors, so I guess low priority. Affected versions: nightly 2022-04-22 does show the ICE, but beta 1.61.0-beta.3 does not show the ICE.
